Clear golden amber head with a dissipating white head. Sweet banana clove aromas that come through strongly in the taste. Not bad.
cloudy, amber, orange, brown, alcohol, caramel, medium body,.. worth a try.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: UPDATED: AUG 5, 2011

Black pour with dark tan head. A beautiful stout. Nose is strong bourbon, alcohol, and carmel/chocolate malts. Taste is bourbon, alcohol, carmel, ane chocolate. Big bodied, thick, and full. An exceptional imp stout.
Light straw color with white head. Faint banana clove qualities. Thin bodied. Pass.
On tap. Too dark in the bar to get a good gauge of appearance but it was darker than i expected. Bittersweet smell that came through on taste as well. Lots of carbonation.
Dark brown pour that appears black in glass with beige head. Chocolate and coffee is prominent. Somewhat thin body. Wouldnt buy again.
Pours clear golden orange with white head. Sweet, hoppy dipa characteristics with only a touch of belgian yeast.

Dark brown pour, black in the glass.  Certainly not the blackest, or thickest imp stout. Substantial beige head. Smell is alcohol, dark fruit, molasses, cocoa. Taste is same plus tobacco. Body is medium to full. Very enjoyable, but there is a certain presence of alcohol esters that is mildly unpleasant. Appearance isnt quite amazing either. Worth a try, though.
Clear amber/copper with white head. Taste is hops, light bread and carmel malt. Light bodied. An okay session beer.
Light brown with white head. Banana, clove, bready malts, wheat. Light body.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Dark brown/ copper with white head. Banana, clove, bready malts, apple cider, boozy. Similar to a quad with a splash of booze added. A big beer. Good but i wasnt in love with it and probably wouldnt buy it again.
Hazy golden straw with a white head. Tastes like a light hefe with a somewhat sour finish. Didnt like it.
Dark brown pour with good head. Smell is molasses, gingerbread, chocolate. Taste is same with smoke and roast, coffee. Body is medium to light for style.
Pours a hazy amber/orange/brown. Nice white head with maybe a touch of pink. Smell and taste were lots of grapefruit, and smaller amounts of pine and hops.
Brown/amber pour with a big white, lasting head with moderate lacing. Nose is sweet malt with a hint of white chocolate. Taste is malt, hops, and a slightly herbal tea finish. Medium bodied. Not bad.
On draft at Slows BBQ. Clear, golden, appearance with a small white head. Smell of apples, slight vinegar. Taste was very light apple/vinegar. Body very thin. Really didnt care for this one at all.
beer_name: Great Lakes Holy Moses White Ale

review_blob: Dark pour, but not the blackest stout ever. Beige head. Aroma is coffee, alcohol, hops. Taste is the same and very bitter. I couldnt figure out where all the bitterness was coming from. Was the the coffee alcohol, or the hops? Actually tasted like it was higher than 7.5% abv. Body was medium for style. Good beer, but a little too bitter and hot to give it an elite rating.
Pour is a cloudy orange/brown with a white head. Aroma is heavy on malt with faint grapefruit, hops. Taste is same. Medium to full bodied for style, heavy mouthfeel. Great beer.
Pours a amber with a white head. Smell of light fruit.and hops, grapefruit. Taste is same and somewhat tangy.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Wild Ale

review_blob: Pours a clear amber with a small white head. Aroma of citrus and hops. Taste is same. Medium bodied for style. This beer is pretty much a DIPA.

Dark brown/mahohany color with a nice beige head. Nice bubbles along edge of glass that lasted awhile. Nose was not particularly strong. Flavor was carmel, dark fruit, figs. Very, very smooth and balanced. Creamy mouthfeel. High drinkability.
Black in the glass. Frothy head with good lacing. Hop aroma. Taste of hops, some roasted malts. Medium body with a creamy mouthfeel. Solid.
beer_name: Black Lotus Dark and Lovely Dark IPA

review_blob: Had this a few days ago. I suppose ot was pretty forgettable. Pale golden color, but a decent head with very thick lacing. Lacking in hops. Reminded me almost of a pilsner
Thin, more like a porter. Dark brown. Not much head. Lots of sweet fudge in the taste.

If youre looking for a big imperial stout, you will be disappointed. Sort of reminds me of Samuel Smith Imperial, if I remember correctly. Tastes a lot like an oatmeal stout with a little extra oomph to it. Thin body for the style. Goes down easy.
On tap at Uptown. Did they serve me the wrong beer or something? What I drank was a brown/amber color, with the taste of a double IPA. fuck they must have served me something else.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada 30th Anniversary Jack & Kens Ale

review_blob: Infected? HUGE head. Lots of carbonation. Very thin. Slight sour, tart flavor. Refreshing. Not really bad, but I didnt particularly care for it.
Clear straw colored pour, with a medium sized white head. Good carbonation. Nice, light hop presence. Refreshing.
Golden brown clear pour. Hop nose.  Cant remember the rest. Ob iously not exactly a.memorable brew.
Light straw color. Hops on the nose. Light, refreshing with light wheat taste.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Rating this beer is all about expectations. For a mainstream lemonade beer, this beer succeeds in many ways. Certainly over the top lemonade flavor and very sweet. Nose is straight lemonade. If youre looking for hops or complexity, this is not the beer for you.
banana, citrus, golden, orange, cloudy, medium sweetness, medium body, sticky,

Hazy dark brown/amber pour with a small head. Nose is plums, raisins, cherries, sugar, booze. Taste is boozy dark fruit and bit medicinal with a strange finish. Carbonation is good and mouthfeel is medium. Odd tasting finish makes this brew a bit unpleasant. Definitely a big beer though, and overall not that bad.

Whats with the low rates on this? This was not a bad beer whatsoever. Hard for me to give a great review of it right now that im a bit buzzed and i had its been a couple hours since i drank it but... Hazy golden/orange/amber pour with a white head. Hops, but not over the top. Belgian characteristics were rather minimal. Certainly worth a try at $5.

Dark brown pour, black in the glass with a big off white head. Characteristics of a black bier or a porter. Roasty malts with slight choco/coffee notes. Good carbonation with a medium bodied mouthfeel. Solid for the style.
had this a few beers back. clean amber/gold color. lots of bitter hops. solid.

Im not really familiar with sours. Is this really considered a sour or a fruit beer? Man im a little too buzzed right now and the beer has been gone for a couple hours. It was decent though. Apple and grape flavors going on. Not bad. L

A beautiful beer. Honey/amber/orange in color with a nice white head that leaves a good fading lace. First sniff is piney hops, but over time that smell gives in to citrus and peppermint. Taste is hops with a solid malt backbone. Medium bodied. Pleasantly surprised.
Im not a big fan of tripels and i wasnt really feeling this when i drank it. It is pretty good for a tripel. Standard qualities.

I only had a few sips of this one at the end of an imperial stout session. Even after having bombarded my taste buds with 3 RISs, I still found this to be a flavorful beer. Reminded me a lot of an IPA with lesser hops. Smell was hops and citrus, with similar taste and a solid malt presence as well. Decent looking beer as well. Solid beer overall for the style.

Great Divide comes through again with an exceptional brew. Very dark and viscous. Reminiscent of regular Oak Aged Yeti with a nice dark chocolate presence. Full bodied with an excellent mouthfeel. Highly recommend.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Chocolate Oak Aged

review_blob: Dark brown pour, minimal head. Smell is coffee and vanilla. Ditto for the taste, with a decent amount of roast as well. Slightly sweet, but not too much. Medium mouthfeel, as expected for a porter. Very good brew for the style.

Dark brown pour with a beige head. Looks a bit thin. Smell is bourbon. Taste is lots of bourbon. After taking a few sips, I could really feel the alcohol warming in my chest. It felt like Id just done a shot of bourbon. Mouthfeel was a bit thin. This beer really reminded me of an imperial porter, it wasnt very robust. There was a significant gob of sediment at the bottom of the bottle. Kind of gross.
beer_name: Big Sky Ivan the Terrible Imperial Stout - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: This is a pretty pilsener. I had Atwater Block Uber Ursa yesterday, and while it was an decent beer, this one is much prettier. Gold in color, with a decent head, and slight lacing. Good hops. Nice pils.
clear amber pour. little head. hop forward but with a slight sort of flat sweetness. amazing? no. but solid.
Roasty, toasty, with the characteristics of a very robust porter. Medium bodied. Solid.

December 2010 12oz bottle. Pale straw color. small white head with no lacing. Nose is a bit of skunk. Taste is bitter hops. This is a great success for an Atwater Block beer, the few others Ive tried from them have been awful.
